The paper focuses on path prediction using video as input, which is a task of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with predicting the movement of pedestrians and vehicles, which falls under the scope of robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various approaches for understanding the environment and internal state, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing to some extent, as it discusses datasets used to evaluate path prediction methods, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
